echo "Register No.: 1947235"
echo 
echo -ne "Enter no of levels : "
read level
#temp=$level
#to print first half

	while [ $i -gt 0 ]
	do

		((--i))
	done
	echo

	while [ $i -gt 0 ]
	do

		((--i))
	done
	echo

#to print first half

	#temp=`expr $i - 1`
	temp=$i
	while [ $i -ge 0 ]
	do
		echo -ne "${tempArray[$temp]}"
		((--i))
	done
	echo
done

        #temp=`expr $i - 1`
        temp=$i
        while [ $i -ge 0 ]
        do
                echo -ne "${tempArray[$temp]}"
                ((--i))
        done
        echo
done

#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>

int mutex=1,full=0,empty=10,x=0;

int wait(int s) {
	return (--s);
}

int signal(int s) {
	return (++s);
}

void producer() {
	mutex=wait(mutex);
	full=signal(full);
	empty=wait(empty);
	x++;
	printf("\nProducer produces the item %d" ,x);
	mutex=signal(mutex);
}

void consumer() {

	mutex=wait(mutex);
	full=wait(full);
	empty=signal(empty);
	printf("\nConsumer consumes item %d" ,x);
	x--;
	mutex=signal(mutex);
}


int main() {

	int n;
	void producer();
	void consumer();
	int wait(int);
	int signal(int);

	printf("\n1. Producer \n 2. COnsumer \n 3. Exit ");
	while(1) {
		printf("\n Enter Your Choice : ");
		scanf("%d", &n);
		switch(n) {
			case 1: if((mutex==1)&&(empty!=0))
					producer();
				else
					printf("Buffer is full");
				break;

			case 2: if((mutex==1)&&(full!=0))
					consumer();
				else
					printf("Buffer is empty");
				break;
			
			case 3:
				exit(0);
				break; //No need anyway
		}
	}

	return 0;

}
^C
